<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-53-0335 </DOCNO><TEXT>In 1987 the German gas industry was able to register an increase in sales,related to weather conditions and number of connections, of around 10%,in a market situation, what is more, characterized by very low energyprices and with primary energy consumption remaining almost at the previousyear's level. The contribution of natural gas in primary energy consumptionrose thereby to 16.6%. Sales dropped in the first half of 1988 as a resultof the weather conditions. For the German gas industry the most significantchange in energy policy was the decision of the Federal Government tolevy a tax on natural gas in future.</TEXT></DOC>